---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
title="Weiqi — Privacy Policy"
description="Privacy policy for the Weiqi mobile app — an offline Go board with rules, scoring, beginner AI, SGF import/export, and review."
>
<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
    Privacy Policy for Weiqi
</h1>
<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">
    <strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-05-07
</p>

<div class="prose prose-lg prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
    Weiqi is an offline Go (Weiqi) board application for Android.
    <strong>We do not collect, transmit, sell, or share any personal data.</strong>
    All your data stays on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
    We do not collect any personal information. Weiqi has no user accounts,
    no login, no analytics, no advertising SDKs, no crash reporting, and no
    telemetry. The app does not make network requests.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Stored on Your Device</h2>
    <p>
    The app stores the following information locally on your device only:
    </p>
    <ul>
    <li>
        Saved games and move history, so you can resume play and review past
        games (stored in a local SQLite database on your device).
    </li>
    <li>
        App settings and preferences such as board size, theme, and tutorial
        progress (stored using Android's standard SharedPreferences).
    </li>
    <li>
        SGF (Smart Game Format) files that you choose to import or export.
    </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
    This data never leaves your device unless you explicitly export or share
    an SGF file using your device's share sheet. You can remove all locally
    stored data at any time by uninstalling the app or clearing its storage
    in your device's system settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Permissions</h2>
    <p>
    Weiqi only uses standard Android system services and does not request
    sensitive permissions such as location, contacts, camera, or microphone.
    </p>
    <ul>
    <li>
        <strong>File access</strong> — only when you explicitly choose to
        import or export an SGF file. The app uses Android's system file
        picker; we do not scan or read any other files on your device.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Sharing</strong> — when you tap "share" on an SGF file, the
        app hands the file to Android's standard share sheet. The app itself
        does not transmit any data.
    </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
    Weiqi does not include third-party analytics, advertising, crash
    reporting, or tracking services. The app is built with the Flutter
    framework and uses standard open-source packages (such as
    <code>sqflite</code>, <code>shared_preferences</code>,
    <code>file_picker</code>, and <code>share_plus</code>) purely for local
    storage and OS integration. None of these are used to collect personal
    data.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
    Weiqi is suitable for all ages. Because the app does not collect any
    information from anyone, it does not knowingly collect information from
    children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
    If we ever change this policy, we will update the "Last updated" date
    above and post the new version at the same URL. Material changes will
    be reflected in the app's Play Store listing.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:
        <a href="mailto:prathammpatel@outlook.com">prathammpatel@outlook.com</a>
    </p>
    </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
